Sentencas: This paper reports and discusses composite interconnect materials that were modified from La0.7Ca0.3CrO3- (delta) (LCC) by addition of Re doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for improved conductivity at relative low temperatures.
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that the addition of small amounts of RDC (ReO1.5 doped Ce02) into LCC dramatically increased the electrical conductivity.
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For the best system studied, LCC + 5 wt% SDC (Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9), LCC + 3 wt% GDC (Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9) and LCC + 3 wt% YDC (Y0.2Ce0.8O1.9), the electrical conductivities reached 687.8, 124.6 and 104.8 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C in air, respectively.
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of the specimens, LCC + 3 wt% SDC, LCC + 1 wt% GDC and LCC + 2 wt% YDC in H-2 at 800 degrees C were 7.1, 3.8 and 5.9 S cm-1, respectively.
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With the increase of RDC content, the relative density increased, indicating that RDC served as an effective sintering aid in enhancing the sinterability of the powders.
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) at 30-1000 degrees C in air increased with the increase of the RDC content.
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen permeation measurements indicated a negligible oxygen ionic conduction, indicating that the efficiency loss of a solid oxide fuel cell by permeation is negligible for the general cell design using LCC + RDC as interconnect.
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Therefore, the composite materials La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 are very promising interconnecting ceramics for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: High performance composite interconnect La0.7Ca0.3CrO3/20 mol% ReO1.5 doped CeO2 (Re = Sm, Gd, Y) for solid oxide fuel cells
